.\" Manpage for simple_shell.
.TH simple_shell 1 "2021-15-08" GNU "simple_shell user manual"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- A mini version UNIX shell (command line interpreter)
.SH SYNOPSIS
In case you get the source code make sure you run gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.br
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a prompt where a user can enter a path to a known shell script and execute it
along with arguments
.SH USAGE
The following are the commands that can be run
.br
.B /bin/ls:
- Lists everything in current working directory
.br
.B exit:
- exits out of the shell and returns to original shell
.br
.SH EXAMPLE
Type ./hsh  in your terminal
.br
"$ " empty prompt is shown
.br
"$ /bin/ls" - prints all files in current directory

.SH RETURN VALUES
Result of executed command
.SH BUGS
No known bugs
.SH AUTHOR
Collins Otieno
.br
Nehemiah Kamolu
.SH SEE ALSO
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_shell